WEBVTT

00:05.547 --> 00:07.674
Previously on           
       Let the Right One In...

00:07.716 --> 00:09.843
[Isaiah]              
      Ladies, gentlemen, and...

00:09.884 --> 00:11.011
Can't hear you!

00:11.052 --> 00:12.679
[Eleanor]             
             Excuse me!

00:12.721 --> 00:14.431
Do you need a volunteer?

00:14.472 --> 00:15.849
[whispers] Tell them        
   you're gonna make me disappear.

00:15.890 --> 00:17.517
[Isaiah]              
      I don't know how to do that.

00:17.559 --> 00:18.643
[Eleanor]             
               Trust me.

00:18.685 --> 00:19.936
Hello?

00:21.187 --> 00:24.315
[girl] Yo, that's         
   some Houdini shit right there!

00:24.357 --> 00:26.359
-[scattered laughter]       
              -[whoops]

00:26.401 --> 00:27.861
[Mark]               
 Do you think I could borrow it?

00:27.902 --> 00:29.320
[Zeke]               
          Borrow what? My car?

00:29.362 --> 00:30.363
Yeah, but I'll bring it back.

00:30.405 --> 00:31.906
What do you need it for?

00:31.948 --> 00:34.033
[Mark]   I'm gonna get a text    
            with an address.

00:34.075 --> 00:35.410
There's gonna be a guy there.

00:35.452 --> 00:37.203
I think he might lead me

00:37.245 --> 00:39.748
-to a creature like Ellie.    
             -[knocking]

00:41.291 --> 00:42.667
[Matthew]             
    What are you doing here, sir?

00:42.709 --> 00:44.544
-I drive for a living.       
            -A chauffeur?

00:44.586 --> 00:46.378
I'm thinking you need to      
     find out who owns that car,

00:46.421 --> 00:47.672
and if that man was lying to me.

00:47.714 --> 00:48.965
Yes, sir.

00:49.507 --> 00:51.593
[Fergie]   You think the killer   
           was on something?

00:51.634 --> 00:53.053
[Naomi]   We've got a witness,    
         claims he saw someone

00:53.094 --> 00:54.888
with glowing eyes.

00:54.929 --> 00:56.723
[Fergie]              
     I assume you found no weapons

00:56.765 --> 00:58.390
at the crime scene.

00:58.433 --> 00:59.726
You're saying all this       
          was done by hand?

00:59.768 --> 01:00.894
We're done here.

01:01.686 --> 01:02.896
-[hissing]                
             -[grunting]

01:05.774 --> 01:07.859
-[Mark] Isaiah's father?      
          -[Naomi] Mm-hmm.

01:07.901 --> 01:10.360
intense music

01:10.403 --> 01:12.405
You okay?

01:12.447 --> 01:14.074
When your brother gets hungry,

01:14.115 --> 01:15.699
he's not always himself.

01:15.741 --> 01:17.494
[Claire]              
         My brother is seizing!

01:17.535 --> 01:18.995
[Matthew]             
 He's not seizing. He's starving.

01:20.580 --> 01:21.997
-[Claire] Peter, no!        
      -[man] Help me, help me--

01:22.040 --> 01:24.375
-[snarling]            
            -[screaming]

01:24.417 --> 01:26.628
Stop! Stop, stop!

01:28.880 --> 01:31.091
[drawer closes]

01:31.132 --> 01:33.676
-[footsteps]            
         -[clothes rustling]

01:44.687 --> 01:46.773
[traffic passing in distance]

01:49.609 --> 01:51.528
[phone buzzing]

01:54.489 --> 01:55.740
[Isaiah whispering]        
                  Hey.

01:55.782 --> 01:57.992
Hey. Why are you whispering?

01:58.034 --> 02:00.203
My mom thinks I'm asleep.

02:00.245 --> 02:02.789
-[laughs softly]          
         -Are you in a bathtub?

02:02.831 --> 02:05.375
Yeah, but there's         
        no water or anything.

02:05.416 --> 02:08.086
You sleep in a bathtub?

02:08.128 --> 02:09.963
I don't do             
      a whole lot of sleeping.

02:10.004 --> 02:12.632
-[Naomi]   Isaiah?          
          -That's my mom. Bye.

02:12.674 --> 02:14.634
[thudding in other room]

02:21.015 --> 02:23.393
What are you doing?

02:23.434 --> 02:26.229
-No.                
         -I'm sorry, honey.

02:26.271 --> 02:27.897
You said you would stay,      
            you promised.

02:27.939 --> 02:30.316
That's before I knew        
         the woman next door

02:30.358 --> 02:32.819
was a homicide detective.

02:32.861 --> 02:35.989
-Isaiah's mom?           
                -Yes.

02:36.030 --> 02:38.198
We don't need to leave the city.

02:38.241 --> 02:40.160
We just need to find        
       another place to live.

02:40.201 --> 02:42.787
What about Isaiah?         
      I can't see him anymore?

02:42.829 --> 02:44.497
No.

02:44.539 --> 02:47.959
The faster we do this,       
        the less it'll hurt.

02:48.001 --> 02:49.627
So go grab whatever you need    
          to carry with you

02:49.669 --> 02:52.005
-for the next few days.      
        -Where are we going?

02:52.046 --> 02:54.132
-Motel.              
         -Of course we are.

02:54.174 --> 02:57.135
Look, honey,            
     it's only temporary. Okay?

02:57.177 --> 02:59.345
I'll find us another apartment

02:59.387 --> 03:00.555
and come back here         
       and get the furniture.

03:00.597 --> 03:02.015
I don't care about         
           the furniture!

03:02.056 --> 03:03.349
Keep your voice down.

03:03.391 --> 03:04.767
I finally have a friend here.

03:04.809 --> 03:06.561
I-I know, honey,

03:06.603 --> 03:08.396
but we've only stayed alive

03:08.438 --> 03:10.773
by knowing             
       when it's time to run.

03:10.815 --> 03:12.442
Well, I don't want to run     
              anymore.

03:12.483 --> 03:13.860
-It is not up to you.       
 -Why did you even bring me here?

03:13.902 --> 03:15.528
Enough, Ellie!           
        These walls are thin.

03:15.570 --> 03:17.280
Why am I even alive        
       if I can't do anything

03:17.322 --> 03:18.781
but hide and be alone?!

03:18.823 --> 03:21.117
You need to lower your voice!   
              [grunts]

03:21.159 --> 03:22.869
You can't take away        
           my only friend!

03:22.911 --> 03:25.205
Ellie...

03:26.497 --> 03:28.208
Honey.

03:32.170 --> 03:35.048
I'm not going anywhere.

03:35.089 --> 03:36.841
And if you make me leave,

03:36.883 --> 03:39.344
I'll just wait           
       until you fall asleep,

03:39.385 --> 03:41.888
and I'll walk out into the sun.

03:48.727 --> 03:50.730
[sighs]

03:50.772 --> 03:52.732
slow, dramatic music

03:55.068 --> 03:58.029
[Claire panting]

03:59.614 --> 04:00.949
[Peter slurping]

04:03.785 --> 04:05.411
[snarls quietly]

04:08.748 --> 04:10.792
[retches]

04:14.170 --> 04:17.215
[crying]              
     Get the fuck away from me.

04:17.257 --> 04:19.676
Who was that man?

04:19.717 --> 04:21.094
The less I tell you,        
        the safer you'll be.

04:21.135 --> 04:23.930
But I promise you         
     no one will ever miss him.

04:23.972 --> 04:25.598
You said you stole         
          from blood banks.

04:25.640 --> 04:26.849
We tried everything.

04:28.142 --> 04:29.978
There is no other way.

04:31.145 --> 04:32.689
[cries]

04:36.484 --> 04:39.112
intense music

04:43.157 --> 04:45.868
You fucking liar! Wake up!

04:45.910 --> 04:47.954
Motherfucker!

04:50.290 --> 04:52.041
[whimpers]

04:57.463 --> 04:59.549
[gasps, cries]

05:04.304 --> 05:07.390
[breathes shakily]

05:07.432 --> 05:09.100
Fuck you!

05:18.651 --> 05:21.446
[tape ripping]

05:38.713 --> 05:40.590
Ellie?

05:40.631 --> 05:42.925
Honey?

05:42.967 --> 05:44.427
You awake?

05:46.220 --> 05:48.598
[chuckles softly]

05:48.639 --> 05:50.850
This is not very mature.

05:53.811 --> 05:56.189
Got to go out, okay?

05:57.565 --> 05:58.900
I love you.

05:58.941 --> 06:00.068
[elevator button clicks]

06:02.111 --> 06:03.863
[sighs]

06:05.406 --> 06:07.784
Hey, I thought I heard you.

06:07.825 --> 06:09.202
Look, the kids had         
    such a good time last night,

06:09.243 --> 06:10.578
I was hoping you and Eleanor

06:10.620 --> 06:12.246
might want to           
        come over for dinner.

06:12.288 --> 06:14.749
Uh, that-that's very kind,     
             thank you.

06:14.791 --> 06:17.627
But I'm afraid           
     Eleanor has food allergies.

06:17.668 --> 06:21.089
Oh. I'm sorry.           
        Is it peanuts, or...

06:21.129 --> 06:22.673
Oh, to almost everything.

06:22.715 --> 06:24.217
She can only eat at home.

06:24.258 --> 06:27.136
-Well, that must be hard.     
            -[soft laugh]

06:27.177 --> 06:29.097
But thank you           
         for the invitation.

06:29.138 --> 06:31.849
Well, food or no food,       
     we'd love to have her over.

06:31.891 --> 06:33.309
I mean, what she did

06:33.351 --> 06:34.727
at the talent show         
       last night was just...

06:34.769 --> 06:36.354
Talent show?

06:36.396 --> 06:39.607
She didn't tell you she went    
      to Isaiah's talent show?

06:40.691 --> 06:43.569
Oh, no, yeah, sure. Of course.

06:43.611 --> 06:45.905
Isaiah's in a bit of        
      a rough patch right now.

06:45.947 --> 06:47.532
His dad went AWOL on him,

06:47.573 --> 06:48.825
-and...              
             -I'm sorry.

06:48.866 --> 06:50.243
Yeah, no, what, um...

06:50.284 --> 06:52.245
what I'm trying to say is that

06:52.286 --> 06:54.414
Eleanor's friendship means     
         a whole lot to him.

06:54.455 --> 06:57.542
And it means a lot         
          to Eleanor, too.

06:57.583 --> 06:59.293
Then maybe we should        
          exchange numbers.

07:02.088 --> 07:03.840
So we can set up playdates

07:03.881 --> 07:06.050
without me having to chase     
      you down in the hallway.

07:06.092 --> 07:07.969
[door rattles]

07:13.724 --> 07:14.892
There you go.

07:14.934 --> 07:17.478
Okay... great.

07:17.520 --> 07:18.813
Now you have mine.

07:24.068 --> 07:26.195
tense music

07:29.657 --> 07:31.659
I haven't told Peter yet.

07:31.701 --> 07:33.953
I thought that you         
        would want to do it.

07:39.125 --> 07:41.294
Stay the hell away         
          from my brother.

07:43.838 --> 07:45.465
[door creaks]

07:49.594 --> 07:51.637
[creaks]

08:00.688 --> 08:02.565
I should've warned you.

08:03.691 --> 08:05.442
Dad should've warned me.

08:07.028 --> 08:08.321
Where is he?

08:15.119 --> 08:17.622
Did he die alone?

08:21.584 --> 08:23.377
Good.

08:31.802 --> 08:33.846
Peter.

08:34.931 --> 08:38.684
When you were...

08:38.726 --> 08:40.353
feeding...

08:42.855 --> 08:44.815
...could you hear me        
         calling your name?

08:44.857 --> 08:45.816
It's hard to explain.

08:45.858 --> 08:47.610
Try.

08:51.239 --> 08:54.534
The room gets brighter,      
           and I-I can...

08:54.575 --> 08:57.411
I can hear             
      heartbeats and breathing.

09:00.581 --> 09:04.377
It's like I'm not in control,   
       but I don't even care,

09:04.418 --> 09:07.547
'cause when I start to drink,   
          it feels so good.

09:09.257 --> 09:11.384
Sometimes people try        
        to fight back, but...

09:11.425 --> 09:13.553
-It doesn't hurt.         
                -No.

09:14.554 --> 09:16.722
It's better than that,        
           it feels good.

09:17.807 --> 09:19.934
I like when they fight back.

09:19.976 --> 09:22.687
Peter, it's not you.

09:22.728 --> 09:24.105
It's the virus.

09:24.146 --> 09:25.398
It's hijacking your brain,

09:25.439 --> 09:27.108
incentivizing you to feed

09:27.149 --> 09:28.734
by flooding you with dopamine   
        and norepinephrine...

09:28.776 --> 09:30.528
But the virus is me, right?

09:31.904 --> 09:33.197
What are you talking about?

09:33.239 --> 09:34.615
Dad said it's not just       
            in my cells,

09:34.657 --> 09:36.742
it's in my DNA,          
        which means it is me.

09:36.784 --> 09:39.370
Fuck Dad.

09:39.412 --> 09:42.832
What I saw in there is not you.

09:42.873 --> 09:44.917
[groans, shudders]

09:44.959 --> 09:46.877
Are you okay?

09:46.919 --> 09:48.588
Do you want me           
        to get any pain meds?

09:48.629 --> 09:51.632
No. Dad tried painkillers     
    on me and they don't do shit.

09:53.634 --> 09:55.886
Honestly, the only time      
    I haven't been in pain is...

09:55.928 --> 09:57.763
When you were feeding.

09:59.974 --> 10:03.269
tense music

10:03.311 --> 10:05.354
-               
        -[indistinct chatter]

10:11.068 --> 10:14.614
Jesus.               
        If I get shot today,

10:14.655 --> 10:16.282
and the ambulance         
       wants to bring me here,

10:16.324 --> 10:17.742
please tell them Mount Sinai.

10:17.783 --> 10:19.869
-[baby wailing]          
          -I was born here.

10:22.288 --> 10:23.914
-I'm fucking with you.       
              -[laughs]

10:23.956 --> 10:25.625
But quit acting like        
     the Bronx is the Wild West,

10:25.666 --> 10:27.835
-Mr. Forest Hills.         
       -Hey, when I was a kid,

10:27.877 --> 10:29.253
Forest Hills was not        
           "Forest Hills."

10:29.295 --> 10:31.464
Mm-hmm, and I'm sure        
          you kept it real.

10:31.505 --> 10:33.466
-It was not bougie.        
            -[chuckling]

10:33.507 --> 10:35.301
On my block we had         
          two nail salons,

10:35.343 --> 10:36.844
a fish market,

10:36.886 --> 10:39.305
and an ATM that only gave out   
          ten-dollar bills.

10:41.724 --> 10:44.352
We're here to talk         
        to Christina Delgado.

10:44.393 --> 10:47.146
Morning, Detectives.        
       We spoke on the phone.

10:47.188 --> 10:48.981
Ms. Delgado is           
       on a lot of pain meds,

10:49.023 --> 10:51.359
so she might be a little erratic 
    when you're speaking to her.

10:51.400 --> 10:52.943
But she is conscious and stable.

10:52.985 --> 10:54.195
And you said it was unclear

10:54.236 --> 10:55.696
if the attacker used        
          a weapon on her?

10:55.738 --> 10:57.490
Well, she didn't think so,

10:57.531 --> 11:00.534
but he must have used something 
         because, uh-- Look.

11:00.576 --> 11:03.746
How could anyone use        
    their bare hands to do that?

11:11.170 --> 11:13.673
Hi, Christina, I'm Naomi.     
      This is my partner, Ben.

11:13.714 --> 11:15.758
We're homicide detectives.

11:18.678 --> 11:20.888
Do you mind if we ask you     
          a few questions?

11:22.181 --> 11:24.517
Can you remember what happened?

11:24.558 --> 11:26.352
[EKG beeping]

11:26.394 --> 11:28.270
[panting softly]

11:28.312 --> 11:31.190
[weakly]              
          He was so strong.

11:31.232 --> 11:35.986
I tried to fight him,       
     as hard as I could, but...

11:36.028 --> 11:39.365
when I hurt him...

11:39.407 --> 11:41.325
...he started laughing.

11:42.702 --> 11:44.704
Do you remember          
        what he looked like?

11:45.788 --> 11:48.165
[Christina]            
             His eyes...

11:48.207 --> 11:51.669
they were all shiny.

11:51.711 --> 11:53.504
Like cat's eyes.

11:55.256 --> 11:57.925
[Naomi] What else do you      
     remember about the attack?

11:57.967 --> 11:59.510
[Christina]            
            I don't know.

11:59.552 --> 12:01.262
I blacked out.

12:02.763 --> 12:06.392
And when I woke up,        
     he was standing over me...

12:07.518 --> 12:11.230
...and then he was just gone.

12:11.272 --> 12:13.065
Like magic.

12:13.107 --> 12:14.817
He disappeared.

12:14.859 --> 12:17.403
[sobbing] I'm so afraid      
     he's gonna come back again.

12:17.445 --> 12:18.863
-He won't.             
               -No...

12:18.904 --> 12:21.365
-You're safe here.         
         -I want to go home.

12:21.407 --> 12:23.075
I want to see my daughter.

12:23.117 --> 12:25.327
-I'll go get the nurse.      
    -No, I don't want the nurse!

12:25.369 --> 12:27.580
I want to go home!

12:27.621 --> 12:29.749
-Why can't I feel my hands?!    
                -Shh.

12:29.790 --> 12:31.751
What did he do to me?

12:31.792 --> 12:34.086
[yelling]

12:34.128 --> 12:36.172
tense, suspenseful music

12:39.133 --> 12:41.385
pulsing, somber music

13:21.926 --> 13:25.763
[chuckles]             
        Am I all covered up?

13:25.805 --> 13:28.474
I don't want my doorman to see   
     me in last night's outfit.

13:28.516 --> 13:31.310
-No one will ever know.      
             -[chuckles]

13:33.979 --> 13:36.273
Uh, what are you doing Saturday?

13:36.315 --> 13:38.275
I thought that we were       
          just having fun.

13:38.317 --> 13:41.445
Uh, yeah, but, uh,         
    we can have fun on Saturday.

13:41.487 --> 13:44.990
-[phone ringing]          
      -Oh, it's, uh... my car.

13:45.032 --> 13:46.992
You know,             
      if you hang on a second,

13:47.034 --> 13:48.327
I can give you a ride home.

13:48.369 --> 13:51.205
That's okay,            
       my Uber's here already.

13:51.247 --> 13:55.125
But thank you for ordering me   
        a Black, by the way.

13:55.167 --> 13:57.795
Very classy.

13:57.837 --> 14:00.214
-Mm.                
         -[chuckles softly]

14:03.217 --> 14:05.010
Get home safe.

14:08.138 --> 14:12.101
-Girlfriend?            
       -Uh, no. Just a friend.

14:12.142 --> 14:15.271
-Her dorm doesn't have a curfew? 
          -Dawg, fuck you.

14:15.312 --> 14:16.939
No, she's an accomplished woman.

14:16.981 --> 14:18.607
-She's a dancer...         
                -Oh.

14:18.649 --> 14:20.776
Ah, no. Not that kind       
     of dancer-- You know what?

14:20.818 --> 14:23.320
None of your damn business.    
              My keys?

14:23.362 --> 14:25.114
I need to ask you         
         for one more thing.

14:25.155 --> 14:26.949
Oh, great.             
             No problem.

14:26.991 --> 14:30.369
Gave you a car, job--       
        W-What else you need?

14:30.411 --> 14:31.871
My condo?

14:31.912 --> 14:33.873
[hip-hop playing]

14:35.583 --> 14:39.211
Get your ass inside,        
      I'll make you breakfast.

14:44.675 --> 14:46.719
[indistinct chatter]

14:51.599 --> 14:53.058
[boy 1]              
      Yo! That's the magician.

14:53.100 --> 14:55.519
[boy 2] That was mad cool     
      what you did last night.

14:55.561 --> 14:58.689
-[girl] How'd you do it?      
      -A magician never tells.

14:58.731 --> 15:00.316
[boy 3]              
               Up top!

15:04.069 --> 15:06.989
And you were out there trying   
     to trash talk him and shit?

15:07.031 --> 15:08.824
He made y'all look stupid.

15:08.866 --> 15:10.826
[children]             
                Ooh!

15:10.868 --> 15:12.870
[laughter]

15:13.454 --> 15:17.833
Omelette aux fines herbes,    
        a little   pomme rosti

15:17.875 --> 15:19.335
and, for              
     the pièce de résistance...

15:19.376 --> 15:20.961
[laughs] Oh, your         
       grandmother's biscuits.

15:21.003 --> 15:22.463
Come on, now.

15:22.504 --> 15:23.881
[both laughing]

15:23.923 --> 15:26.216
Oh, wow.

15:26.258 --> 15:28.218
[inhales]

15:28.260 --> 15:29.762
[exhaling]

15:29.803 --> 15:31.597
Don't tell me you're not hungry.

15:31.639 --> 15:34.558
I-- No, it's just that, um...

15:34.600 --> 15:37.436
I really don't eat         
         like this anymore.

15:37.478 --> 15:40.940
Oh, I see what this is.

15:40.981 --> 15:45.069
You don't think you should be   
         able to enjoy food

15:45.110 --> 15:46.362
because she can't.

15:48.948 --> 15:51.116
So what do you eat?

15:51.158 --> 15:52.910
Uh... just, you know,

15:52.952 --> 15:55.955
a lot of energy bars        
           and smoothies.

15:55.996 --> 15:57.122
Oh, God.

15:57.164 --> 15:59.667
[laughs]              
          It's not too bad.

15:59.708 --> 16:00.960
There's this protein powder--

16:01.001 --> 16:02.461
Honestly, come on, man. Uh-uh.

16:02.503 --> 16:04.588
You need to stop talking      
       and-and eat your food.

16:04.630 --> 16:07.049
Wow, where'd you get        
         the Sevruga caviar?

16:07.091 --> 16:11.095
Oh, we did a little catering    
   for some Wall Street assholes.

16:11.135 --> 16:12.805
I kept the leftovers.

16:13.889 --> 16:15.224
[sighing deeply]

16:15.265 --> 16:17.643
[Zeke]               
       Is that a smile I see?

16:17.685 --> 16:19.019
-Wow.               
                -Oh.

16:19.061 --> 16:20.854
[both laughing]

16:22.147 --> 16:23.816
Brother, I'm fucked.

16:26.944 --> 16:29.196
There's a cop           
        who lives next door.

16:29.238 --> 16:31.657
You moved in next to a cop?

16:31.699 --> 16:33.826
That's not the worst part.

16:35.327 --> 16:36.996
There's something         
        I got to do tonight.

16:38.372 --> 16:39.832
It's not that.

16:39.873 --> 16:41.500
I'm taking care of loose ends,

16:41.541 --> 16:44.795
and there's a chance        
      I'll get caught doing it.

16:44.837 --> 16:45.837
So maybe don't do it.

16:45.879 --> 16:48.589
Then I'll definitely get caught.

16:48.632 --> 16:51.677
This cop, she knows        
         I have a daughter.

16:51.719 --> 16:53.846
If I get arrested,

16:53.886 --> 16:57.348
I need you to go get Ellie     
         and bring her here.

16:59.184 --> 17:02.688
All I'm asking is         
    you give her a place to hide.

17:05.315 --> 17:07.401
And then what?

17:08.027 --> 17:10.154
Oh, no, she won't be hungry    
          for a long time--

17:10.195 --> 17:11.488
Look, I won't kill for her.

17:11.530 --> 17:12.823
-I'm not asking you to.      
             -So, what?

17:12.865 --> 17:14.158
Am I supposed to let her

17:14.199 --> 17:15.492
-fend for herself?         
                -No.

17:15.534 --> 17:16.827
-Does she know how to do that?   
                -No!

17:16.869 --> 17:19.413
She never has           
         and she never will.

17:20.622 --> 17:21.999
She's not a monster.

17:22.041 --> 17:24.043
So, then, I'd have         
         to be the monster.

17:28.630 --> 17:30.340
[sighs softly]

17:31.759 --> 17:35.012
-Does she know you found me?    
                -No.

17:35.054 --> 17:37.890
If I tell her, I know       
    she'll want to see you, so--

17:37.931 --> 17:40.559
And I want to see her, too.

17:45.439 --> 17:47.649
I want to see my goddaughter.

17:52.613 --> 17:54.573
gentle, tranquil music

17:56.909 --> 17:58.952
[phone whooshing]

18:25.104 --> 18:26.897
["The 30th"            
       by Billie Eilish playing]

18:26.939 --> 18:31.026
When I saw the ambulances    
           on the shoulder

18:31.068 --> 18:34.071
I didn't even think of     
             pullin' over

18:34.113 --> 18:39.118
I pieced it all together    
           late that night

18:40.494 --> 18:45.499
And I know you don't      
         remember calling me

18:46.834 --> 18:50.087
But I told you even then

18:50.129 --> 18:53.132
You looked so pretty

18:53.173 --> 18:56.802
In a hospital bed

18:56.844 --> 19:00.139
I remember you said

19:00.180 --> 19:03.851
You were scared

19:03.892 --> 19:07.479
And so was I

19:07.521 --> 19:10.899
What if it happened to you   
         on a different day?

19:10.941 --> 19:14.528
On a bridge where there wasn't 
          a rail in the way?

19:14.570 --> 19:17.906
Or a neighborhood street    
     where the little kids play?

19:17.948 --> 19:21.410
Or the Angeles Crest      
       in the snow or the rain?

19:21.451 --> 19:24.955
What if you weren't alone,   
      there were kids in the car

19:24.997 --> 19:27.875
What if you were remote,    
      no one knows where you are

19:27.916 --> 19:31.128
If you changed anything,    
     would you not have survived?

19:31.170 --> 19:32.421
You're alive, you're alive

19:32.462 --> 19:36.175
You're alive

19:50.564 --> 19:52.691
So I've made all the burial    
            arrangements.

19:53.984 --> 19:56.528
Arthur's cemetery plot        
        is already paid for.

19:59.740 --> 20:01.325
Just thought you'd want to know.

20:01.366 --> 20:04.036
You can stick him in        
 a potter's field for all I care.

20:05.495 --> 20:07.206
He was your father.

20:09.750 --> 20:11.710
Some of us don't get one.

20:14.338 --> 20:17.174
What exactly did my dad      
            have on you?

20:17.216 --> 20:18.717
Excuse me?

20:18.759 --> 20:20.719
You're his henchman,        
     he must've had something--

20:20.761 --> 20:22.137
-I'm not a henchman.        
             -Yeah, no.

20:22.179 --> 20:24.056
I'm sure you fancy         
         yourself a soldier.

20:25.432 --> 20:27.184
I saw your tattoo.

20:27.226 --> 20:30.771
I served my country,        
 yeah, in ways you can't imagine.

20:31.980 --> 20:34.107
And when I came home,       
            I struggled.

20:35.442 --> 20:36.902
Your dad took me in.

20:38.278 --> 20:39.613
It was an honor to serve him.

20:39.655 --> 20:41.365
I saw what you do for my dad.

20:42.574 --> 20:45.869
There is nothing          
         honorable about it.

20:52.751 --> 20:54.711
Can I help?

20:54.753 --> 20:56.296
Make sense of your dad's--

20:56.338 --> 20:59.299
You have a lot of expertise    
         in pain management?

21:00.801 --> 21:02.594
Some.

21:08.308 --> 21:11.103
I'm good, thanks.

21:13.814 --> 21:16.108
Actually...

21:18.485 --> 21:22.447
you said before that you used   
     to donate blood for Peter?

21:22.489 --> 21:24.616
-Yeah.               
       -Would you do it again?

21:24.658 --> 21:26.451
He just fed.

21:26.493 --> 21:28.287
I'm aware.

21:28.328 --> 21:29.955
It's not for that.

21:32.457 --> 21:33.792
Will you do it?

21:33.834 --> 21:35.460
Of course.

21:36.628 --> 21:38.213
I work for you now.

21:42.843 --> 21:44.428
[door opens, closes]

21:47.055 --> 21:48.807
Mr. Johnson asked me        
         to come get Isaiah.

21:48.849 --> 21:51.601
[teacher]             
           Okay. Go ahead.

22:01.278 --> 22:04.823
Do you know why          
    Mr. Johnson wants to see me?

22:04.865 --> 22:06.491
Am I in trouble?

22:15.375 --> 22:16.960
You want an ice cream sandwich?

22:17.002 --> 22:19.838
They keep it locked up,      
      but Manny found the key.

22:19.880 --> 22:22.090
You can have one...

22:23.383 --> 22:25.385
...if you tell me         
       how you did that trick.

22:28.055 --> 22:29.264
I can't.

22:29.306 --> 22:31.475
A magician never tells.

22:31.516 --> 22:32.559
No.

22:33.810 --> 22:35.645
I don't know how I did it.

22:35.687 --> 22:37.189
He wants me            
        to believe that shit.

22:37.230 --> 22:39.691
-It's the truth.          
    -[Abel] Why you lying to me?

22:39.733 --> 22:41.985
I swear I don't know        
           how she did it!

22:42.027 --> 22:45.238
Maybe you can get out of this   
             with magic.

22:45.280 --> 22:46.948
No, please! Help!

22:55.457 --> 22:57.376
[Mark knocking on door]      
               Ellie?

22:57.417 --> 22:58.794
Can you come out?

22:59.961 --> 23:03.715
-[Ellie] What for?         
     -Someone wants to see you.

23:21.441 --> 23:23.235
[Zeke laughs softly]

23:23.276 --> 23:25.821
gentle, lighthearted music

23:29.282 --> 23:31.159
How's my girl?

23:33.912 --> 23:35.664
-You got bigger.          
                -Mm.

23:35.705 --> 23:37.666
[laughing]

23:37.707 --> 23:41.002
[sighs] It's muscle.        
          It's all muscle.

23:41.044 --> 23:43.588
-Yeah, right.           
          -[Zeke chuckles]

23:43.630 --> 23:45.757
Oh, look at you.

23:49.136 --> 23:50.429
[smacks lips]

23:52.305 --> 23:54.474
Looks like you got yourself    
    a little nest in there, huh?

23:54.516 --> 23:56.059
-It's cool, right?         
              -Mm-hmm.

23:56.101 --> 23:57.477
Check it out.

24:04.734 --> 24:07.696
-I just made that.         
                -Hmm.

24:07.737 --> 24:09.406
Wow.

24:12.451 --> 24:14.953
Maybe I'll get you to do      
      one for me someday, huh?

24:14.995 --> 24:16.997
-[chuckles]            
                -Hmm?

24:28.758 --> 24:31.219
[Zeke]   Your dad tells me      
        you've got a new friend.

24:31.261 --> 24:34.431
Yeah, he's super nice and funny.

24:34.473 --> 24:36.099
-Oh.                
       -Not like most people.

24:36.141 --> 24:37.893
Okay.               
      Are most people not nice?

24:37.934 --> 24:39.811
Eh, not the ones we meet.

24:44.191 --> 24:45.775
Everything okay?

24:45.817 --> 24:48.945
Yeah. Yeah, no.          
   He's just not texting me back.

24:48.987 --> 24:50.447
[chuckles softly]         
              Weird...

24:50.489 --> 24:52.157
Ah, he's at school.

24:52.199 --> 24:54.993
A teacher probably asked him    
       to put his phone away.

24:55.035 --> 24:57.871
And most boys           
         are bad at texting.

24:59.206 --> 25:01.041
Isaiah's not.

25:06.922 --> 25:08.673
[Elizabeth]            
           So much scarring.

25:08.715 --> 25:11.301
I'm gonna have to go through    
 the dorsal vein this time, okay?

25:15.764 --> 25:17.849
[crinkling]

25:18.934 --> 25:21.520
slow, somber music

25:36.409 --> 25:38.078
I never said thank you.

25:39.037 --> 25:41.081
[chuckles softly]

25:51.925 --> 25:54.553
[Mark]               
        How did she seem to you?

25:54.594 --> 25:56.429
Lonely.

26:01.893 --> 26:04.187
Why do you think you might     
         get caught tonight?

26:05.772 --> 26:07.399
If I tell you,           
        you're an accessory.

26:07.440 --> 26:09.025
Oh, just say it.

26:12.779 --> 26:14.948
I have to move a body.

26:17.242 --> 26:18.743
Hmm.

26:21.621 --> 26:23.623
Well...

26:26.543 --> 26:29.129
Sounds like            
      you might need a lookout.

26:33.133 --> 26:35.176
[dog barking in distance]

26:47.981 --> 26:51.067
Christina was attacked       
             right here.

26:51.109 --> 26:55.697
And the only other witness     
   says the perp fled... that way.

26:58.158 --> 27:00.118
Makes no fucking sense.

27:00.160 --> 27:03.580
Mm-mm. Christina said       
        he just disappeared.

27:03.622 --> 27:06.791
[sighs]              
     Got to love that morphine.

27:21.806 --> 27:24.351
-[laughs] Oh, no. Come on.     
             -Oh, yeah.

27:24.392 --> 27:25.977
Go grab the crowbar        
           from the trunk.

27:26.019 --> 27:27.270
I got my J's on.

27:27.312 --> 27:30.315
-[chuckles] Your what?       
             -OG, baby.

27:30.357 --> 27:33.109
I cannot believe the captain    
       lets you wear sneakers.

27:33.151 --> 27:35.236
I told him I had          
         plantar fasciitis.

27:35.278 --> 27:36.946
Oh.

27:36.988 --> 27:39.783
Well, you're welcome to just go 
      down wearing your socks.

27:41.159 --> 27:43.328
[clicking tongue]

27:43.370 --> 27:46.122
[laughing]             
                Man.

27:46.164 --> 27:48.041
[chuckles]

27:56.007 --> 27:58.176
suspenseful music

28:42.345 --> 28:45.098
[breathing heavily]

29:04.701 --> 29:08.747
Man-Manhattan North Homicide    
             to Central.

29:08.788 --> 29:11.082
[dispatcher]            
     Go, Manhattan North Homicide.

29:11.124 --> 29:13.126
I have a 10-54.

29:13.168 --> 29:17.464
Hmm. I have a 10-54,        
           multiple DOAs,

29:17.505 --> 29:19.549
in the sewer tunnels underneath

29:19.591 --> 29:22.385
Craven and Leggett?

29:22.427 --> 29:24.262
Have the precinct         
          concerned 85 me.

29:24.304 --> 29:27.307
I'll need the patrol supervisor, 
   and notify the medical examiner

29:27.348 --> 29:28.892
and crime scene.

29:28.933 --> 29:30.769
Also, Central,           
       send ESU to my location

29:30.810 --> 29:32.437
for an evidence search.

29:32.479 --> 29:34.147
[dispatcher]            
 Copy, Manhattan North Homicide.

29:40.987 --> 29:45.116
Hey, set up a perimeter      
       and work your way back.

29:48.119 --> 29:49.078
Shit.

29:49.120 --> 29:50.622
Fuck.

29:50.663 --> 29:52.290
[exhales]

30:00.673 --> 30:02.133
[sighs]

30:05.512 --> 30:07.472
[banging nearby]

30:16.523 --> 30:18.566
[grunting]

30:19.609 --> 30:21.528
Police!              
         Hands on your head!

30:23.029 --> 30:26.074
[laughs]

